  "prompt": "How do I play gem TD in DOTA2 when there is no internet?",
  "response": "As of my last update, Gem TD, like many custom games for Dota 2, requires an initial internet connection to be downloaded and played. Once you've already downloaded and played Gem TD, you may be able to play it offline, but there are some limitations and steps you should follow:\n\n1. **Initial Download**: First, ensure you have downloaded Gem TD while connected to the internet. You need to have played it at least once while online.\n\n2. **Steam Offline Mode**: To play without an internet connection, you need to set Steam to Offline Mode:\n   - Open Steam while you're still connected to the internet.\n   - Click on \"Steam\" in the upper left corner of the Steam client.\n   - Select \"Go Offline...\" from the dropdown menu.\n   - A pop-up will appear asking if you want to restart in Offline Mode. Click on \"Restart in Offline Mode.\"\n\n3. **Launching Dota 2**: After restarting Steam in Offline Mode, launch Dota 2 from your Steam library.\n\n4. **Accessing Custom Games**: Once Dota 2 is open, you should be able to access custom games you've previously downloaded, such as Gem TD, in your Arcade library.\n\n5. **Gameplay Limitations**: Be aware that many custom games, including Gem TD, might have limited functionality when played offline. Features that depend on server connectivity, leaderboards, or multiplayer modes may not work.\n\nKeep in mind that game updates, patches, or version compatibility changes in Dota 2 and its custom games might prevent them from functioning correctly offline in the future. It's always a good idea to occasionally go online to update your games.",
